==Latin==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|la|res loquitur ipsa|rēs loquitur ipsa}} ([http://books.google.is/books?id=bXGJuX1mDrwC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA201])

===Etymology===
From {{m|la|rēs||thing}} + {{m|la|ipsa||herself}}, the feminine of {{m|la|ipse||himself}} because {{m|la|rēs}} is a feminine word + {{m|la|loquitur||she speaks}} the third-person form of {{m|la|loquor||I speak}}. Literally meaning "the thing itself speaks" or "the matter itself speaks".

===Phrase===
'''[[res#Latin|rēs]] [[ipsa]] [[loquor#Latin|loquitur]]'''

# the thing [[speak]]s for [[itself]]

